# Project Structure Guide

This is a Go-based batch SQL execution and schema synchronization tool with a well-organized structure.

## Main Components

- [main.go](mdc:main.go) - Application entry point
- [Makefile](mdc:Makefile) - Build and development commands

## Internal Packages

The `internal` directory contains all the core application code:

- [internal/bootstrap](mdc:internal/bootstrap) - Application initialization
- [internal/handler](mdc:internal/handler) - HTTP request handlers
- [internal/middleware](mdc:internal/middleware) - HTTP middleware components
- [internal/pkg](mdc:internal/pkg) - Internal utility packages
  - [internal/pkg/response](mdc:internal/pkg/response) - Standard response handling
- [internal/router](mdc:internal/router) - Route registration and configuration
- [internal/service](mdc:internal/service) - Business logic implementation

## Build Artifacts

- [build](mdc:build) - Directory for build outputs

